content.thinking:
Great! So the fix was to change:
```c
extern char yr_lowercase[256];
extern char yr_altercase[256];
```
to:
```c
extern uint8_t yr_lowercase[256];
extern uint8_t yr_altercase[256];
```

This is the fix for the unsigned to signed conversion issue. The bug was that with `char` (which is signed), non-ASCII values (128-255) would be converted to negative values when used in comparisons or array indexing, causing the character class matching to fail.

Now let me check if this change is actually in the buggy version. Let me look at the current globals.h file.

Perfect! So the buggy version still has:
```c
extern char yr_lowercase[256];
extern char yr_altercase[256];
```

Instead of:
```c
extern uint8_t yr_lowercase[256];
extern uint8_t yr_altercase[256];
```

And there's also missing the `#include <inttypes.h>` include. This is definitely the bug. Let me also check libyara.c to see if it has the same issue.

